race.comment: ABBY'S CROSSWORD (1) settled worse than midfield then wound up strong to be beaten narrowly over 1400m at this track last start. Fitter for two runs back from a spell and the progression to a mile looks perfect at this stage of the campaign. VOTING RIGHTS (12) disappointed when making her Victorian debut a month ago. The rider reported blinkers and more ground were required which she gets today. Recent Flemington jump-out winner who is a genuine chance. SHARK PARK (6) has not appeared since a moderate debut at Cranbourne ten months ago. Has been to the jump-outs three times recently so should be forward enough to run well. SO REGAL (7) led for home but was cut down late over 1562m at Mt Gambier recently. Tougher task this time but is very fit and capable of a top-three finish. KAZZA JOY (5) has had plenty of chances but could sneak into the frame at her first run on the home track.
